    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="10" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Campbell</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Office</hi> U. S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Military Telegraph, War
                                    Department.</hi>
                        </placeName>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#center">[From <placeName>New York</placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-11-09">November 9,
                                    1866</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Hon. W. H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of
                                    State</hi>:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Arrived with General Sherman last evening; have received instructions
                            sent here by mail, and by Plumb. I find in them no instructions as to
                            how I am to proceed to Mexico, nor any orders placing any vessel at my
                            disposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LEWIS D. CAMPBELL, <hi rend="italic">Metropolitan
                                Hotel.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
